x4freetext: The errors are compounded from the
statistical counting errors and the uncertainties
introduced in drawing a line shape which subtracts out
the continuum neutrons. This uncertainty in the
background subtraction introduces most of the error in
the cross section at the backward angle, where the
analog (p,n) cross sections are small, and no
appreciable error at the forward angles, where the
However, in no case is the error in the cross sections
less than 7%, which represents an estimate
of the absolute accuracy of the detector efficiency.
believes that author extracted a part of (p,n)
reaction which leaves the reaction product to the
lowest level of the isobaric analogue state. There is
no information on the excitation energy of the
isobaric analog state in the article, and compiler
believes use of IAS-NUMB=0 is the proper coding way.
The user must be careful of these values.
